## Component Composition

### Building Complex Components

```tsx
function ConversationCard({ conversation }) {
  return (
    <Card className="hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>{conversation.title}</CardTitle>
        <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          {formatDate(conversation.created_at)}
        </p>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <p>{conversation.overview}</p>
        <div className="flex gap-2 mt-4">
          <Button variant="outline" size="sm">View</Button>
          <Button variant="ghost" size="sm">Edit</Button>
        </div>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Accessibility**: Use Radix UI components for built-in accessibility
2. **Styling**: Use Tailwind utility classes
3. **Composition**: Compose complex components from simple ones
4. **Dark Mode**: Ensure components work in both light and dark modes
5. **Responsive**: Make components responsive with Tailwind breakpoints
6. **Type Safety**: Use TypeScript for component props

